				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA: Master of Disguise<a name="62100"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 15 04 12:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It is also one of the few AAs a bard can have fun with. I mean really, how much fun is it to mitigate damage or avoid an incoming attack. Although these AAs make your character better and might be the difference in living through an encounter, they are not fun to play with.
<br />

<br />
Now changing how you look, using abilities you don't normally get, and exploring places you are KoS in can add some cheap thrills and excitement you just cant get from lightning reflexes.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /></span></td>
