				<td colspan="2"><span>Iksar form from mask does not give any regen.  I read that the enchanter illusion forms DO give a slight (like 1 hp per tick) regen, but not sure on that.  All illusions seem to have SOME racial characteristic -- usually vision.  Which is not always good - having Barbarian form bless you with night-blindness is not exactly a selling point.  However barb form does give you the ability to slam.  Almost every illusion has some small benefit.  Most of the time in my xp group I am pulling and in my raids, I am part of the pull team and directing tactics, so I generally just don't have time to mess with illusions.  Hence, spending valuable AAs on an ability that just allows me to avoid hitting a right click seems a big waste of AA - but as I said, that's just me.  Those of you who think this AA is the reason to buy OOW, knock yourselves out.  If you read stuff I have posted in the past, you should know I am the first person to suggest it is ok to spend points on stuff just for fun as well as the practical stuff.  All I was saying is that I don't see this as adding that much fun OR practicality.  Obviously there are other ways to view it.
